    public interface GroupableAction
    GroupableAction.java --- An Interface that each action which can be performed as a group must implement.

    P H - 03.08.2017

    • Method Detail

      • canPerformGrouped

        boolean canPerformGrouped()
        Function for checking if the action can be performed as a group.
        Returns:
        true if the action can be performed as a group. False if not.

      • performGrouped

        boolean performGrouped(javaGOAP.IGoapUnit groupLeader,
                       javaGOAP.IGoapUnit groupMember)
        Function for actually performing the action as a group. This function is only called when mirroring the leader's action towards the other members of it's group and is not called for the leader himself.
        Parameters:
        groupLeader - reference to the leader of the group.
        groupMember - the current Unit that is mirroring the leader's action.
        Returns:
        true if the action was performed successfully, false if not.

      • defineMaxGroupSize

        int defineMaxGroupSize()
        Function for defining the maximum number of members of the group.
        Returns:
        the maximum number of members the group is allowed to have.

      • defineMaxLeaderTileDistance

        int defineMaxLeaderTileDistance()
        Function for defining the max range for a Unit trying to join a leader's group.
        Returns:
        the max distance in TilePositions that a leader is allowed to be away from the Unit.
